Target: OntoForest is an ontology developed for creating a digital twin for the forest.

Comment: Land covered with trees and shrubs
Label: Woodland

Comment: Land not covered with trees.
Label: Non Woodland

Comment: Areas have not been checked against the latest images and will be monitored in future updates and either updated to reflect forest type or removed from the dataset. (The Supplied grant scheme polygons and supplied FC new planting polygons).
Label: Assumed Woodland

Comment: Woodland dominated (more than 80% of the area) by trees which do not have needles.
Label: Broadleaved

Comment: Woodland dominated (more than 80% of the area) by trees which have needle-like leaves.
Label: Conifer

Comment: Woodland where young tree stems are repeatedly cut down to near ground level to put out new shoots from their stump or roots.
Label: Coppice

Comment: Woodland where young tree stems, mainly large broadleaved trees, are repeatedly cut down to near ground level to put out new shoots from their stump or roots.
Label: Coppice with Standards

Comment: Established woodland, but which may have failed to achieve woodland cover.
Label: Failed

Comment: Areas of woodland where the trees have been harvested or felled.
Label: Felled

Comment: Land recently converted from some other land use to woodland.
Label: Ground Prep

Comment: Polygonal areas mapped by NIWT but not mapped by NFI but investigation of the archive images shows a higher density than at present. These have been included for future monitoring.
Label: Low Density

Comment: Woodland predominantly covered (more than 50% of the area and less than 80%) by broadleaved trees and exhibits intermediate characteristics between Conifer and Broadleaved woodland.
Label: Mixed Mainly Broadleaved

Comment: Woodland predominantly covered (more than 50% of the area and less than 80%) by coniferous trees and exhibits intermediate characteristics between Conifer and Broadleaved woodland.
Label: Mixed Mainly Conifer

Comment: A plant community characterised by vegetation dominated by shrubs, often also including grasses, herbs, and geophytes.
Label: Shrub

Comment: Area where the interpreter is uncertain of the IFT/IOA to be used.
Label: Uncertain

Comment: Woodland where trees that have been windblown.
Label: Windblow

Comment: Areas where planting is clearly visible but the trees cannot yet be allocated between Conifer and Broadleaved due to their immaturity. These areas can be on either land new to woodland or where a felled crop has been replaced.
Label: Young Trees

Comment: Land that may contain a cereal crop or pasture.
Label: Agriculture Land

Comment: Bare ground or rock.
Label: Bare Area

Comment: If cloud or shadow areas obscure woodland detail and it is difficult to allocate one of the above IFTs, then digitise a new boundary line feature around the area of uncertain forest type.
Label: Cloud or Shadow

Comment: A predominantly grassy area - may or may not be agricultural.
Label: Grassland

Comment: Normally labelled within OS MasterMap, areas of even colour.
Label: Open Water

Comment: Not covered by the above (e.g. gorse, rhododendron, bracken, heather etc)
Label: Other Vegetation

Comment: Linear feature, possibly shadow evidence of poles, pylons or even the cables/lines.
Label: Powerline

Comment: A place with evidence of change from vegetation to geology; sand, slate, rock etc. Active quarries could have buildings, and heavy plant tracks leading into the quarry.
Label: Quarry

Comment: Linear feature; depending on location can be fairly straight or meander through woodland
Label: River

Comment: Linear feature; often fairly straight with gentle bends or turning circles
Label: Road

Comment: Buildings within woodland areas; may include gardens surrounding the buildings.
Label: Urban

Comment: Possible shadow evidence of turbines, normally in groups.
Label: Windfarm
